white jury has acquitted two for
mer Ku Klux Klansmen charged
with numbering Lemuel Penn, a
Negro educator from Washington.


The jury deliberated three
hours and Is minutes last night
before acquitting Joseph Howard
Sims, Al, and Cecil William

charges of conspiracy and are

Fletcher A. Wiley. FL, senior
at the United States Air Force
Academy, in Colorado. spent the
Labor Day weekend as the guests
of Mr.. and Mrs. Edward Banks.


Cadet Wiley graduated from
Shortridge High School. Indiana
polls, Ind, 1860. He enrolled
at the Air Force Academy in July.
1861.


During his three years there
he has maintained a high scholar
ship index and is presently on the
superintendent list for high
grades and military excellence.


He played football for two
years, and is member of the
choir and the international af-
fairs forum.


He is entered in the masters
program which will enable him to
receive credits toward a mas
ter's degree before completing
his four years at the Academy.


Wiley toured Europe last year
with the choir and he spent five
weeks there this summer on a
private trip. He hopes to return
to Coventry, England this fall.


After completing his cadet
training he plans to pursue law
studies ateither Yale or Harvard.


He is the son of Mrs. Mildred
Wiley, 1880 Congress, Indiana
polls.
